Wash and dry all produce. Preheat the oven to 400 degrees. Cut the @Yukon Gold Potatoes{12%ounce} into ½-inch wedges. Core and quarter the @Roma Tomato{2}. Mince the @Garlic{2%cloves}.

Toss the potatoes on one side of a foil-lined #baking sheet{} with a drizzle of @Olive Oil{drizzle} and a pinch of @Salt{pinch} and @Pepper{pinch}. On the other side, toss the tomatoes with a drizzle of @Olive Oil{drizzle}, the garlic, and a pinch of salt and pepper. Place in the oven for ~{25-30%minutes}, tossing halfway through. Roast until the potatoes are crispy and the tomatoes have shriveled.

In a #medium bowl{}, combine the @Panko Breadcrumbs{1/2%cup}, @Dried Oregano{1%teaspoon}, @Paprika{1%teaspoon}, @Mozzarella Cheese{1/2%cup}, a drizzle of @Olive Oil{drizzle}, and a pinch of salt and pepper. Place the @Chicken Breasts{12%ounce} onto another lightly oiled baking sheet. Season on all sides with salt and pepper, then rub with a drizzle of olive oil. Press the panko mixture onto the top of each chicken breast, firmly pressing with your palm to adhere. Pile the topping as high as possible, however you may have some left over.

Place the chicken in the oven until the topping is golden brown, and juices run clear when pierced with a knife, ~{15-20%minutes}.

Thinly slice the @Basil{1/2%ounce}. Serve the mozzarella-crusted chicken with the potato wedges and garlic-roasted tomatoes alongside. Sprinkle with basil and enjoy!

> Think of this dish as a new take on Chicken Parmesan. Herbs, breadcrumbs, and mozzarella make up a crispy, cheesy coating on juicy chicken. Instead of marinara, garlicky roasted tomatoes add a sweet punch. We've added crispy potatoes because, why not?